away from any populated areas,

1667
01:57:56,157 --> 01:58:00,295
and allowing him to execute
a forced landing in an open field.

1668
01:58:09,903 --> 01:58:12,291
I heard a loud metallic bang.

1669
01:58:13,182 --> 01:58:14,994
We pitched nose down.

1670
01:58:16,877 --> 01:58:17,812
No control.

1671
01:58:17,875 --> 01:58:21,351
Yeah. First Officer Evans
testimony confirms the same.

1672
01:58:24,393 --> 01:58:25,711
I want to show you something.

1673
01:58:30,506 --> 01:58:32,347
Nothing's happening, uh...

1674
01:58:33,144 --> 01:58:36,611
Its remote control isn't working,
apologies, I can do this manually.

1675
01:58:47,976 --> 01:58:51,419
This is the jackscrew on the
tail assembly that articulates

1676
01:58:51,431 --> 01:58:55,264
the horizontal stabilizer...
also known as the elevator.

1677
01:58:55,636 --> 01:59:00,072
As you can see, the threads on
this screw are almost entirely gone.

1678
01:59:00,645 --> 01:59:06,510
This part was suggested as a maintenance
replacement in January of 2011.

1679
01:59:06,578 --> 01:59:08,138
It was never replaced.

1680
01:59:08,365 --> 01:59:12,440
It had an additional 1200 hours
of flight on it. It finally failed.

1681
01:59:12,813 --> 01:59:17,647
Our investigators have concluded
that the jackscrew snapped

1682
01:59:17,734 --> 01:59:21,474
and the elevator was frozen
in a fixed position,

1683
01:59:21,832 --> 01:59:26,720
locking the elevator in a down position
which forced the plane into a dive.

1684
01:59:26,987 --> 01:59:30,859
The loss of the elevator was,
and I quote our report,

1685
01:59:30,899 --> 01:59:34,576
“a catastrophic event, from
which recovery was improbable

1686
01:59:34,592 --> 01:59:37,029
and stable flight, impossible.”

1687
01:59:40,685 --> 01:59:41,805
Mr. Whitaker...

1688
01:59:42,777 --> 01:59:47,454
I want to talk about the days leading
and the hours leading up to the accident.

1689
01:59:47,645 --> 01:59:50,572
But before I do, I want to
remind you that you are under oath,

1690
01:59:50,581 --> 01:59:54,080
and that any testimony you'll give here
today will be considered admissable

1691
01:59:54,089 --> 01:59:56,813
in any subsequent hearings
or criminal proceedings.

1692
01:59:56,968 --> 01:59:59,133
Do you understand what that means?

1693
02:00:01,174 --> 02:00:04,687
Captain Whitaker, for the record
I need you to verbalize your answer.

1694
02:00:05,704 --> 02:00:08,131
Uh, I'm sorry.
Yes, I understand.

1695
02:00:08,925 --> 02:00:12,704
On the three days leading up
to the accident: Tuesday, October 11th,

1696
02:00:12,721 --> 02:00:16,250
Wednesday, October 12th
or Thursday, October 13th,

1697
02:00:16,260 --> 02:00:20,510
did you consume any alcohol
