1698
02:00:21,571 --> 02:00:22,935
No, I did not.

1699
02:00:23,255 --> 02:00:27,112
On the morning of the accident,
Friday, October 14th,

1700
02:00:27,261 --> 02:00:32,520
did you consume any alcohol,
or ingest any chemicals or drugs

1701
02:00:32,521 --> 02:00:36,083
that may have impaired your
ability to perform your job?

1702
02:00:36,716 --> 02:00:38,186
No, I did not.

1703
02:00:39,263 --> 02:00:43,433
Mr. Whitaker, do you now or
have you ever had a problem

1704
02:00:43,435 --> 02:00:47,642
with alcohol dependency,
alcoholism or drug addiction?

1705
02:00:47,809 --> 02:00:48,979
No.

1706
02:00:51,303 --> 02:00:53,816
Okay, Mr. Whitaker, we’re about done.

1707
02:01:00,645 --> 02:01:05,343
Due to the severe turbulence in the
early part of the flight, you asked

1708
02:01:05,344 --> 02:01:08,883
the flight crew to suspend the beverage
service on the plane, is that correct?

1709
02:01:09,132 --> 02:01:12,696
Yes, That's correct, I suspended
the drink service on the plane.

1710
02:01:12,745 --> 02:01:17,492
Are you aware that our investigators
found two single-service vodka bottles

1711
02:01:17,493 --> 02:01:18,941
in the galley trash bin?

1712
02:01:21,455 --> 02:01:23,382
Yeah, I'm aware of that.

1713
02:01:24,029 --> 02:01:26,440
There were five crew members on board

1714
02:01:26,448 --> 02:01:29,081
that who would have had access
to the beverage trolley.

1715
02:01:29,415 --> 02:01:31,386
Less than an hour after the accident,

1716
02:01:31,394 --> 02:01:34,475
blood was taken from each
of these crew members, yourself,

1717
02:01:34,971 --> 02:01:39,578
first officer Evans, flight
attendant Margaret Thomason...

1718
02:01:39,975 --> 02:01:45,371
and posthumously from Camelia
Satou, and Katerina Marquez.

1719
02:01:46,514 --> 02:01:49,732
A toxicology analysis was performed and...

1720
02:01:50,420 --> 02:01:52,517
three of these tests came back negative,

1721
02:01:52,518 --> 02:01:56,585
one was disqualified for
technical reasons, and one...

1722
02:01:57,089 --> 02:02:02,118
tested positive for alcohol.
It registered a .17 blood alcohol level.

1723
02:02:02,119 --> 02:02:03,616
Are you aware of that?

1724
02:02:04,636 --> 02:02:06,526
Yeah. I'm aware of it now.

1725
02:02:13,276 --> 02:02:17,367
Miss Marquez was not only a colleague,
but you knew her outside of work,

1726
02:02:17,375 --> 02:02:19,449
is that correct?

1727
02:02:20,452 --> 02:02:22,132
Outside of work...

1728
02:02:23,054 --> 02:02:24,335
No, not really.

1729
02:02:24,447 --> 02:02:27,113
Did you know Miss Marquez
had a drinking problem?

1730
02:02:28,216 --> 02:02:29,429
No, I did not.

1731
02:02:29,538 --> 02:02:31,863
Did you ever see her drink to excess?

1732
02:02:34,382 --> 02:02:35,848
No, I did not.

1733
02:02:35,898 --> 02:02:38,802
Were you aware that she was
twice treated for alcohol addiction,

1734
02:02:38,806 --> 02:02:42,835
the last time was 16 months ago
and paid for by SouthJet Airlines?

1735
02:02:44,291 --> 02:02:45,691
No, I did not.

1736
02:02:56,058 --> 02:03:02,618
Is it your opinion... that Katerina
Marquez... drank on that flight?

1737
02:03:14,229 --> 02:03:16,024
Could you repeat the question?

1738
02:03:16,778 --> 02:03:21,338
Is it your opinion that Katerina
Marquez drank on that flight?

1739
02:03:33,431 --> 02:03:34,714
I’m sorry. My what?

1740
02:03:34,847 --> 02:03:35,967
Your opinion, Captain.

1741
02:03:36,198 --> 02:03:39,430
Since her toxicology report
is the only toxicology report

1742
02:03:39,442 --> 02:03:43,968
that is admissable in this hearing, and
she in fact tested positive for alcohol,

1743
02:03:43,969 --> 02:03:47,873
is it your opinion that Katerina Marquez

1744
02:03:47,894 --> 02:03:51,598
drank those 2 bottles
of vodka on the plane?

1745
02:04:03,149 --> 02:04:06,365
I’m sorry Mr. Whitaker, I couldn’t
hear you. What did you say?

1746
02:04:09,177 --> 02:04:11,143
I said, "God, help me."

1747
02:04:11,914 --> 02:04:14,763
Yes, well. However, is it your opinion-

1748
02:04:14,774 --> 02:04:16,208
It's my opinion...

1749
02:04:16,467 --> 02:04:18,287
Trina did not...

1750
02:04:18,638 --> 02:04:20,190
drink that Vodka.

1751
02:04:20,859 --> 02:04:22,112
Excuse me, Mr. Whitaker?

1752
02:04:22,128 --> 02:04:23,698
She saved the boy’s life, that's-

1753
02:04:23,699 --> 02:04:25,412
Could you speak louder, Captain Whitaker?

1754
02:04:25,420 --> 02:04:27,961
Trina Marquez did not drink the vodka.

1755
02:04:29,546 --> 02:04:31,653
Because I drank the vodka.

1756
02:04:34,632 --> 02:04:35,809
Objection!

1757
02:04:36,721 --> 02:04:38,637
Please be seated sir. This-

1758
02:04:39,567 --> 02:04:40,687
Sir.

1759
02:04:40,838 --> 02:04:41,715
– I drank the vodka bottles-

1760
02:04:41,716 --> 02:04:43,312
– I drank the vodka bottles-
– Did you hear what I said, I object!

1761
02:04:43,320 --> 02:04:45,843
Please be seated sir,
this is not a court room.

1762
02:04:45,913 --> 02:04:47,363
Well, I object anyway!

1763
02:04:48,849 --> 02:04:51,128
I drank the vodka bottles on the plane.

1764
02:04:53,029 --> 02:04:57,676
Captain Whitaker. On the three nights
before the accident, October 11-

1765
02:04:57,687 --> 02:05:02,778
October 11, October 12 and 13th
and 14th, I was intoxicated.

1766
02:05:02,789 --> 02:05:05,771
I drank all of those days, I drank...

1767
02:05:06,381 --> 02:05:07,781
in excess.

1768
02:05:09,211 --> 02:05:12,083
– On the morning of the accident-
– I was drunk.

1769
02:05:20,145 --> 02:05:21,596
I'm drunk now.

1770
02:05:28,131 --> 02:05:29,856
I'm drunk right now...

1771
02:05:30,490 --> 02:05:32,013
Miss Block...

1772
02:05:38,920 --> 02:05:40,605
because I'm alcoholic.

1773
02:06:06,490 --> 02:06:07,924
That was it.

1774
02:06:11,560 --> 02:06:13,042
I was finished.

1775
02:06:15,002 --> 02:06:16,437
I was done.

1776
02:06:19,429 --> 02:06:25,169
It was as if I had reached
my life long limit... for lies.

1777
02:06:26,452 --> 02:06:29,458
I could not tell one more lie.

1778
02:06:32,984 --> 02:06:34,708
And maybe I'm a sucker.

1779
02:06:36,795 --> 02:06:39,245
Because if I had told just one more lie,

1780
02:06:39,735 --> 02:06:42,300
I could have walked away
from all that mess...

1781
02:06:43,009 --> 02:06:46,588
kept my wings, kept my
false sense of pride...

1782
02:06:49,232 --> 02:06:54,120
and most importantly, I could have avoided
being locked up in here with all of you,

1783
02:06:54,842 --> 02:06:57,714
nice folks for the last 13 months.

1784
02:07:01,329 --> 02:07:02,834
But I'm here.

1785
02:07:03,824 --> 02:07:05,824
And I'll be here for at least the...

1786
02:07:06,504 --> 02:07:09,056
next four or five years.
And that's fair.

1787
02:07:12,937 --> 02:07:15,841
I betrayed the public trust. I did.

1788
02:07:16,031 --> 02:07:20,215
That’s what the judge explained to me.
I had betrayed the public trust.

1789
02:07:22,003 --> 02:07:25,142
The FAA, they took away
my pilot's license.

1790
02:07:27,112 --> 02:07:28,399
And that's fair.

1791
02:07:29,372 --> 02:07:32,963
My chances of ever flying
again are slim to none.

1792
02:07:35,002 --> 02:07:36,648
And I accept that.

1793
02:07:39,473 --> 02:07:42,541
I got a lot of time to think
about it, the all of it.

1794
02:07:45,202 --> 02:07:46,418
Doing some writing.

1795
02:07:48,387 --> 02:07:52,420
I wrote letters to each of the
families that had lost loved ones.

1796
02:07:55,662 --> 02:07:57,683
Some of ‘em were able
to hear my apology...

1797
02:07:59,881 --> 02:08:01,331
some of ‘em never will.

1798
02:08:03,165 --> 02:08:05,694
I also apologized to...

1799
02:08:06,905 --> 02:08:11,434
all the people that tried to help me...
along the way, but I...

1800
02:08:13,113 --> 02:08:15,767
couldn't or wouldn't listen.

1801
02:08:19,075 --> 02:08:20,963
People like my wife...

1802
02:08:24,700 --> 02:08:26,361
My ex-wife...

1803
02:08:30,751 --> 02:08:32,241
My son.

1804
02:08:35,536 --> 02:08:38,644
And again like I said, you know,
some of them will...

1805
02:08:41,057 --> 02:08:43,586
never forgive me, some of them won't...

1806
02:08:46,025 --> 02:08:47,905
But at least I'm sober.

1807
02:08:50,523 --> 02:08:53,779
I thank God for that,
I’m grateful for that.

1808
02:08:56,606 --> 02:08:58,510
And this is gonna sound really stupid

1809
02:08:58,511 --> 02:09:01,142
coming from a man who’s
locked up in prison...

1810
02:09:03,554 --> 02:09:05,692
but for the first time in my life...

1811
02:09:07,202 --> 02:09:08,755
I’m free.

1812
02:09:22,294 --> 02:09:25,081
Whitaker.
You got a visitor.

1813
02:10:02,555 --> 02:10:04,886
– You have 40 minutes.
– Okay.

1814
02:10:15,358 --> 02:10:17,157
Look at you, boy.

1815
02:10:17,759 --> 02:10:18,965
How you doing?

1816
02:10:19,288 --> 02:10:20,840
– Good.
– You look good.

1817
02:10:22,146 --> 02:10:23,972
Com'on, sit down.

1818
02:10:25,642 --> 02:10:28,598
This is a surprise.
Did you get that gift I sent you?

1819
02:10:28,608 --> 02:10:29,269
– Yeah.
– Yeah?

1820
02:10:29,285 --> 02:10:30,558
– Yeah, I got it.
– You like it?

1821
02:10:30,559 --> 02:10:31,679
– Yeah.
– Good...

1822
02:10:34,128 --> 02:10:37,244
– How's your mom?
– Fine. She's alright.

1823
02:10:39,010 --> 02:10:42,875
My College counselor wanted
me to come in... interview you.

1824
02:10:43,930 --> 02:10:44,945
Me?

1825
02:10:45,131 --> 02:10:48,441
Yeah. I'm writing essays
for College applications.

1826
02:10:48,504 --> 02:10:49,624
Good.

1827
02:10:49,950 --> 02:10:51,416
I need your help.

1828
02:10:51,729 --> 02:10:53,129
So you got it.

1829
02:10:54,375 --> 02:10:59,218
And then... this essay.
The essay that I have to write...

1830
02:11:01,020 --> 02:11:07,455
it's called... “the most fascinating
person... that I’ve never met.”

1831
02:11:18,226 --> 02:11:19,904
So...

1832
02:11:24,468 --> 02:11:25,935
Who are you?

1833
02:11:35,042 --> 02:11:36,579
That's a good question.

